  "description":[
    "The Traffic Management and Engineering Program manages Boston&rsquo;s transportation network to provide safe, efficient travel throughout the City.  This is accomplished through maintenance of traffic signal timings using the City&rsquo;s computerized traffic signal system; design and review of new/upgraded traffic signal installations; review of proposed roadway and transit projects, review and approval of private development plans; licensing of on-street construction; permitting of special events; review and modification of existing parking rules and regulations; and working with neighborhood groups to improve traffic and pedestrian safety on residential streets."
